## Regulatory Scan (March 28, 2026)

The regulatory picture has gotten significantly more complex since the Prediction Index report was published three weeks ago. The situation is now bifurcated:

**1. CFTC is building the framework (SUPPORTIVE)**
Published an Advanced Notice of Proposed Rulemaking on March 16. Comment period open until April 30. Principles-based approach. Chairman Selig publicly backs Kalshi in state legal fights.
- [CFTC ANPR](https://www.cftc.gov/PressRoom/PressReleases/9194-26) | [CoinDesk](https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2026/03/12/prediction-markets-get-tailored-u-s-guidance-from-former-foe-cftc)

**2. Congress is trying to kill sports/election contracts (HOSTILE)**
"Prediction Markets Are Gambling Act" introduced March 23 by Schiff/Curtis (bipartisan). Would ban contracts on sports, elections, war. A separate Merkley/Raskin bill targets the same. If either passes, it guts Kalshi and Polymarket's business.
- [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/03/26/prediction-markets-sports-election-war-legislation-kalshi-polymarket.html) | [Axios](https://www.axios.com/2026/03/26/prediction-market-ban-bill-jeff-merkley)

**3. States are going criminal (AGGRESSIVE)**
Arizona AG filed 20 criminal charges against Kalshi (first-ever criminal case). Michigan AG sued. 39 state AGs formed coalition. 11 states issued cease-and-desists. States claim $600M in lost gambling tax revenue.
- [NPR](https://www.npr.org/2026/03/17/nx-s1-5751165/kalshi-criminal-charges-arizona) | [Michigan AG](https://www.michigan.gov/ag/news/press-releases/2026/03/05/ag-nessel-files-lawsuit-against-kalshi)

**4. Insider trading is the scandal driving all of this**
Someone made $400K+ on Maduro's ouster before it happened. Six wallets made $1.2M on the Iran strike (one account "Magamyman" traded 71 minutes before news, profited $553K). These incidents are the political ammunition behind every bill.
- [Harvard Law](https://corpgov.law.harvard.edu/2026/03/25/from-iran-to-taylor-swift-informed-trading-in-prediction-markets/) | [Fortune](https://fortune.com/2026/03/24/kalshi-polymarket-congress-senate-updated-policies-insider-trading-gambling/)

**So what for LEVER:**
- Sports is the kill zone. LEVER should stay far away from sports market contracts.
- Crypto, macro, and geopolitical categories are NOT targeted by any of these bills.
- Insider trading enforcement WILL eventually reach leveraged prediction products. Worth flagging to ADVISOR now.
- CFTC ANPR comment deadline (April 30) is worth monitoring; the final rules will shape what is legal infrastructure.

